SECTION 5 — RULES
════════════════════════════════════════════════════

1. location.getState().navigationId > 1 is the correct
   Angular way to check if there is navigation history.
   Do NOT use window.history.length — that includes
   browser history from other sites and gives wrong results.

2. The CSS gradient (.bg-gradient-layer) stays on ALL
   routes always. Only the canvas element toggles.
   Never remove the gradient layer from any route.

3. app-page-header is sticky (position: sticky, top: 0)
   NOT fixed. Fixed headers require padding-top on every
   page to prevent content hiding behind them.
   Sticky headers scroll with the page until they hit
   the top, then stick — no padding needed.

4. id="discover" on the cards section in landing.component
   is mandatory. Without it the scrollIntoView call
   in goBack() silently fails and user lands at page top.

5. The 400ms setTimeout before scrollIntoView is required.
   Router.navigate() is async — the DOM needs time to
   render the landing page before scrollIntoView can
   find the element. Without the delay it always fails.

6. Do NOT add any solid background to :host on any
   page component. background: transparent is mandatory
   everywhere so the global CSS gradient shows through.

7. Remove the existing back button from ecosystem
   .eco-topbar — it is now handled by app-page-header.
   Do not have two back buttons on ecosystem.

8. On landing page ('/') — app-page-header is NEVER
   rendered. The landing page manages its own header-less
   hero. Do not add app-page-header to landing.component.

