**The key decision here is `location.getState().navigationId > 1`** — this is the only reliable way in Angular to know if there's a previous route in the navigation stack. `navigationId === 1` means this is the first page the user landed on — so clicking back would exit the app. Anything greater than 1 means there's Angular history to go back to. That's what routes the user correctly to the cards section when they open `/ecosystem` directly in a new tab vs when they click into it from the landing page.
